All in all pretty good value for money, but don’t expect the rooms to resemble luxury spa accommodation – they are closer to motel standard.	These are increasingly becoming standard fare in more and more hotels and motels.	The treatment was fine -- pretty much the standard calistoga mud and mineral bath.	The price was right, the rooms were clean and very comfortable, and the mineral pools made the deal that much sweeter.	During our stay, we enjoyed the mud bath, mineral bath and 1 hour massage combination package, went back to our room for a nap, then went out to St. Helen's for a nice dining experience at the Culinary Institute of America.